/i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":20,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Walter Heron was born about 1270, in Northumberland, England, his father, William Heron, was 32 and his mother, Christian Notton, was 32. He married Cristiana De NOTTON about 1280, in Notton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died before 1297, in Silkstone, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1270–Bef 1297":"umbes 1270–enne 1297","1260–1333":"1260–1333","1260–Female":"1260–Surnud","1270–1297":"1270–1297","1277–Male":"1277–Surnud","1280–Male":"1280–Surnud","1257–Female":"1257–Surnud","1289–1323":"1289–1323","1240–1296":"1240–1296","1240–1297":"1240–1297","about 1270":"umbes 1270","October 1289":"oktoober 1289","1297":"1297","1296":"1296","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1323":"1323","1257":"1257","1289":"1289","1333":"1333","1277":"1277","Bef 1297":"enne 1297","10 December 1296":"10. detsember 1296","ABT 1280":"umbes 1280","Newcastle upon Tyne, Northumberland, England":"Newcastle upon Tyne, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Notton, Yorkshire, England":"Notton, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Silkstone, Yorkshire, England":"Silkstone, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hedlestone, Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1270–Bef 1297":"noin 1270–ennen vuotta 1297","1260–1333":"1260–1333","1260–Female":"1260–Kuollut","1270–1297":"1270–1297","1277–Male":"1277–Kuollut","128